history.content:
From what I understand, physics/CS/chem students all have separate seats so it shouldn't affect physics majors.

In case you wanted to enroll in C191 this semester, this was posted on the Physics 101 Piazza:

"Hi all, C191 will be offered in Spring 2023 instead of Fall 2022. As you prepare for Fall 2022 enrollment, please note this update. Feel free to check in with your advisor if you have questions on which courses to take this semester."

From the Physics 101 Piazza:

"Hi all, C191 will be offered in Spring 2023 instead of Fall 2022. As you prepare for Fall 2022 enrollment, please note this update. Feel free to check in with your advisor if you have questions on which courses to take this semester."

Hi,

In light of this enrollment stuff, non CS majors are prevented from enrolling in any upper division CS Class. 

CS C191 is a cross-listed class called Physics C191 for Physics majors. I wanted to confirm that we Physics majors will have reserved seats/enrollment access for this class and this policy is not affecting us in any way.

Thank you.
